Q1)Explain what the simple List component does.
Solution: A list of items can be rendered using the React component called List. SingleListItem components that each display a text item and allow user selection make up the list.

A SingleListItem's background colour turns to green when it is selected, while the others' backgrounds stay red. To maintain track of which SingleListItem is currently selected, the List component uses state.


Each item in the array of props that the List component receives is an object with a text property. With the text and a onClickHandler prop passed to each component, it iterates over this array and creates a SingleListItem component for each item.

When a SingleListItem is clicked, the onClickHandler prop is a function that is called. It changes